init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Now, the US must fight to secure their place in the world again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Meanwhile, Russia is on the rise.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The new UN wants to establish an armed force that they want the US to be part of.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We learn that Russia has developed a rail gun technology.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We do however, accept an offer to share their Fighter Jets.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In order to get the technology from Russia, we agree to a joint military exercise.
